<subSubSection id="C37F655A0578486C41DDF906FBBB1ECB" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="260" pageId="2" pageNumber="259" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDA36D10578486D41DDF906FDA218BD" blockId="2.[151,1437,901,2045]" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="B911EAC30578486D41DDF906FED9199C" bold="true" box="[199,315,1730,1756]" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C654D520578486D4058F906FE7C199C" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1864" box="[322,414,1730,1756]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hecalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B911EAC30578486D4058F906FE7C199C" box="[322,414,1730,1756]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">Hecalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not share the colour patterns of other 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D520578486D4267F906FC3E199C" box="[893,988,1730,1756]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="285" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Hecalini">Hecalini</taxonomicName>
in the Oriental Region and is, therefore, easily recognized. This genus is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D520578486D439CF923FCD41840" authority="Ball" authorityName="Ball" authorityYear="1900" box="[646,822,1766,1792]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Memnonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B911EAC30578486D439CF923FD1C1840" box="[646,766,1767,1792]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">Memnonia</emphasis>
Ball
</taxonomicName>
of the Holarctic Region and Oriental Region (
<collectingCountry id="F37276410578486D444BF922FA721841" box="[1361,1424,1766,1793]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">India</collectingCountry>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF44B200578486D418DF8CEFECF1864" author="Oman, P. W." box="[151,301,1802,1828]" pageId="2" pageNumber="259" pagination="1 - 253" refId="ref14410" refString="Oman, P. W. (1949) The Nearctic leafhoppers (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). A generic classification and check list. Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Washington, 3, 1 - 253." type="journal article" year="1949">
<collectingCountry id="F37276410578486D418DF8CEFF391864" box="[151,219,1802,1828]" name="Oman" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">Oman</collectingCountry>
(1949)
</bibRefCitation>
separated these two genera based on setal density on the side of the pygofer, and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF44B200578486D45A4F8CEFA981864" author="Hamilton, K. G. A." box="[1214,1402,1802,1828]" pageId="2" pageNumber="259" pagination="452 - 453" refId="ref13634" refString="Hamilton, K. G. A. (2000) Five genera of new-world &quot; shovel-headed &quot; and &quot; spoon-bill &quot; leafhoppers (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae: Dorycephalini and Hecalini). The Canada Entomologist, 132, 452 - 453. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / Ent 132429 - 4" type="journal article" year="2000">Hamilton (2000)</bibRefCitation>
by the aedeagal terminal process, so the division between the two genera was unclear. In fact, 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D520578486D458DF8EBFAED1808" authorityName="Ball" authorityYear="1900" box="[1175,1295,1839,1864]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Memnonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B911EAC30578486D458DF8EBFAED1808" box="[1175,1295,1839,1864]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">Memnonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D520578486D418DF896FF11182C" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1864" box="[151,243,1874,1900]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hecalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B911EAC30578486D418DF896FF11182C" box="[151,243,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">Hecalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having: 1) coronal margin bluntly angled to rounded (coronal margin strongly angled to foliaceous in 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D520578486D418DF8B2FF1118D0" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1864" box="[151,243,1910,1936]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hecalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B911EAC30578486D418DF8B2FF1118D0" box="[151,243,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">Hecalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 2) female with pregenital sternite pointed or toothed, tegmina with one black spot at tip of each clavus and usually another near wing tip (female with pregenital sternite rounded, and tegmina without black spot on tip of clavus or wing tip in 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D520578486D40B3F87AFDE71898" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1864" box="[425,517,1982,2008]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hecalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B911EAC30578486D40B3F87AFDE71898" box="[425,517,1982,2008]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">Hecalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 3) aedeagus with branched pair of processes at tip (aedeagus with a pair of unbranched processes at tip in 
<taxonomicName id="4C654D520578486D40CEF826FDD218BC" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1864" box="[468,560,2018,2044]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hecalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B911EAC30578486D40CEF826FDD218BC" box="[468,560,2018,2044]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="259">Hecalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
